核心能力 Competence
■ 文獻搜尋、評析及彙整能力
訓練文獻搜尋、評析及彙整的能力，以培養職能治療專業研究之基礎。 Abilities for literature survey, review, critcism and organization
To train the abilities with regard to the literature survey, review, critcism and organization and establish the research fundamentals in Occupational Therapy■ 研究規劃與執行之能力
研究主題架構之規劃與執行能力之養成，以提升解決職能治療專業研究問題之能力。 Abilities for research planning and implementation
To cultivate the abilities for planning and implementation of a reserach topic and improve the abilities to solve a research question in Occupational Therapy□ 統計分析、問題思考及整合之能力
學習研究統計、數據分析、結果整合，以提升獨立思考和思辨推理之能力。 Abilities for statisitcal analysis, problem reseasoning and integration
To learn the abilities with reagrd to the research statisitcs, data analysis and result interpretation to promote the capacities in independent thinking and reasoning□ 研究結果呈現、論文撰寫及答辯之能力
培養論文撰寫及答辯之能力，以呈現研究結果及應用，提升職能治療研究水準。 Abilities for experimental result representation, thesis writing and defense
To train the abilities with regard to the thesis writing and defense to present the research outcome and implication as well as to promote the research quality in Occupational Therapy■ 理論技能創新與應用能力
培養具有創新與領導的能力，以為專業技能或臨床研究奠基。 Abilities for innovation and application of theories and skills
To cultivate the abilities with regard to the innovation and leadership to establish concrete fundamentals of professional skills and clinical research 

課程概述 Course Description
       This course is designed to provide hands-on experience for students to learn and operate the research apparatuses in our resources. Those apparatuses include instruments for measuring physical properties/dysfunction, psychometric and psychosocial properties, and the research tools used in the pediatric filed. The contents of this course address (1) to understand the basic rationale and background of the apparatus, (2) to conform the instruction and manual of the apparatus and operate the apparatus practically, and (3) to apply the information to research and clinical practice ultimatelyThis course is designed to provide hands-on experience for students to learn and operate the research apparatuses in our resources. Those apparatuses include instruments for measuring physical properties/dysfunction, psychometric and psychosocial properties, and the research tools used in the pediatric filed. The contents of this course address (1) to understand the basic rationale and background of the apparatus, (2) to conform the instruction and manual of the apparatus and operate the apparatus practically, and (3) to apply the information to research and clinical practice ultimately    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    After completing this course, the student will demonstrate the ability to:
1. Understand the research apparatuses which can be utilized in our resources;
2. Understand the basic theories and principles of these instruments;
3. Facilitate a better understanding of the uses, limitations, and construction of common measures of these instruments;
4. Verify the reliability and validity of these apparatus by using cited and reviewed articles;
5. Use one or more of the introduced instruments to conduct a pilot project; and
6. Apply these apparatuses to the further investigations.    

